snippet.textDisplay:
Hello everyone! New or old army or want to know more about BTS? Please take your time to read this. I promise you’ll learn something new:

Part 1 of 3:
BTS, ”Bangtan Sonyeondan” 방탄소년단 in Korean Hangul is roughly translated to ”Bullet Proof Scoutboys”, and that’s why their fans officially got named A.R.M.Y, which also stands for Adorable Representative for Youth. BTS explained the significant meaning behind it. ARMY is military in English, the body armor and military are always together, so it means that their fans will always be together with Bangtan. One of their singles from their 2013 debute album is ”We Are Bulletproof Pt.2”. Since there isn’t an exact correct English translation of Bangtan Sonyeondan, they now internationally go by BTS ”Beyond The Scene”.

BTS is sensational who has broken global barrieres like no other young artists or boybands have before them, both when it comes to race and language. An internationelly successful music group with 7 Korean boys singing in Korean 20 years ago, would just never had happened. They still sometimes struggle acceptance. Although they are famous worldwide, an aspect of BTS that sets them apart from other globally big artists is that they don’t sing in English except for a few lines or words. (and one single ”Waste of me” done with Steve Aoki).
The world has not seen a craziness for any artist like this since The Beatles. They have broken world records after world records, and are even breaking their own too and keep doing. It’s album charts, physical album sales in this digital era, pre-orders, streamings on all kinds of platforms, tweets, selling out concerts at world stadiums with the fastest sell-outs ever. Last tour 5 stadiums sold out in a single day, and tickets to Wembley sold out in 90 minutes which made BTS add more tour dates. These are stadium arenas that only the biggest superstars got to perform at such as Michael Jackson, Paul McCartney, Madonna, Ed Sheeran etc. These artists have problems even filling the arenas, definitely not selling out in within 2 hours from release. Moreover these artists need front acts, middle acts and end acts to attract more ppl, whereas BTS go alone.

Their latest concert film ”Love Yourself in Seoul” (shot on Aug. 26, 2018, at the Olympic Stadium in Seoul during their first leg of the BTS World Tour: Love Yourself, had the biggest worldwide one-day box office ever for a cinema event. The film was released two months after their previous record-smashing film ”Burn The Stage”. The initial run broke One Direction’s record for the highest-grossing event cinema concert production.
"Boy With Luv feat. Halsey" is the biggest 24 hour debute in YouTube History.

In 2018 they were on the cover of Times Magazine. In native S.Korea they are superstars, national icons and have become ”ambassadors” for Korean popular culture. The economy is growing because of them as they have contributed to an impressive large increase of tourism like no other before. BTS alone bring 3.7 billion dollars every year into the S.Korean economy. In Oct 2018 they were awarded the honorable ”Order Of Cultural Merit” by the S.Korean government and president. When they recieved their statuettes, each member was presented with their talents/skills and position in the group.
The 3 rappers are:
*RM (Main rapper, Leader of BTS, possesses incredible producing skills, made amazing contributions by placing #1 on the Billboard 200 with two consecutive albums - the first Korean artist to do so, (now it’s three albums and BTS is the first artists since The Beatles to score 3 #1 albums in less than a year etc).
*Suga (Lead rapper, possesses solid rapping skills, contributes greatly to K-pop being loved by fans all over the world by showcasing incredible talents such as writing lyrics and composing songs).
*J-hope (Main dancer, in charge of the choreography of BTS, possesses excellent dance skills, plays a large role in gathering attention to the world, completing the powerful and elaborate performances of BTS etc).
The 4 vocalists are:
*Jungkook (shown remarkable talents in all fields, including vocals, dance, songwriting and rap, contributed greatly to BTS to spreading out to the world together with Hallyu (the so called the Korean Wave aka Korean popular culture).
*Jimin (Lead Vocalist and Main dancer, acting as an all-around entertainer who possesses not only excellent dancing skills but also amazing vocals etc).
*Jin (Vocalist, shown multi-faceted talents through his deep emotional comprehension, unique vocals, participating in lyrics writing, leading the movement for the globalization of K-pop etc)
*V (Vocalist, singer/songwriter, charge of killing part of the songs with his deep charismatic voice, working to spread Hallyu all over the world etc). After recieving their medals all 7 members gave individual speeches.

Their hard work and multi-talents have made them won the biggest musical Korean awards (so called ”Daesangs”) in the K-music industry multiple times. BTS made an all-win 2019 when winning all the Daesangs in one night. Overall they are the most decorated K-artists ever. (Girl group ”Girl’s Generation” is in 2nd). Their performances (which are always different at every award show) they prepare so much for every year at these award shows are insane.
BTS is invited to perform at this year’s Grammys 2020. The fact that BTS was completely ignored and snubbed though for any award was scandalous without a legit excuse. BTS had the best-selling album 2019 and hit youtube record with ”Boy with luv”. They litterally out-sold all the albums that were nominated for ”Album of the year”. BTS is high-end on all levels, which is something that alot of people have a hard time to admit or accept. Some said BTS aren’t American, but it shouldn’t matter. Look at the categories and all non-American people who were nominated this year and in the past. What’s the difference? However, BTS was the first Korean act to ever perform at the Grammys in 2020 with Lil Nas X and more.

BTS came from nothing (the small, poor, no-name company BigHit Entertainment) and started out as teenagers over 7 years ago. With limited economy BTS lived together in a cheap, small, simple dorm all 7 boys cramped together sharing one toilet and shower etc. There was no lavish living for them. The litterally grew up together like family, and oldest members Jin and Suga used to drive the youngest member Jungkook to school, who was only 12 when he joined their label BigHit, and was 15 years old at their debute. BTS explained the significant meaning behind it. ARMY is military in English, the body armor and military are always together, so it means that their fans will always be together with Bangtan. One of their singles from their 2013 debute album is ”We Are Bulletproof Pt.2”. Since there isn’t an exact correct English translation of Bangtan Sonyeondan, they now internationally go by BTS ”Beyond The Scene”.

BTS is sensational who has broken global barrieres like no other young artists or boybands have before them, both when it comes to race and language. An internationelly successful music group with 7 Korean boys singing in Korean 20 years ago, would just never had happened. They still sometimes struggle acceptance. Although they are famous worldwide, an aspect of BTS that sets them apart from other globally big artists is that they don’t sing in English except for a few lines or words.  (and one single ”Waste of me” done with Steve Aoki). 
The world has not seen a craziness for any artist like this since The Beatles. They have broken world records after world records, and are even breaking their own too and keep doing. It’s album charts, physical album sales in this digital era, pre-orders, streamings on all kinds of platforms, tweets, selling out concerts at world stadiums with the fastest sell-outs ever. Last tour 5 stadiums sold out in a single day, and tickets to Wembley sold out in 90 minutes which made BTS add more tour dates. These are stadium arenas that only the biggest superstars got to perform at such as Michael Jackson, Paul McCartney, Madonna, Ed Sheeran etc. These artists have problems even filling the arenas, definitely not selling out in within 2 hours from release. Moreover these artists need front acts, middle acts and end acts to attract more ppl, whereas BTS go alone.

Their latest concert film ”Love Yourself in Seoul” (shot on Aug. 26, 2018, at the Olympic Stadium in Seoul during their first leg of the BTS World Tour: Love Yourself, had the biggest worldwide one-day box office ever for a cinema event. The film was released two months after their previous record-smashing film ”Burn The Stage”. The initial run broke One Direction’s record for the highest-grossing event cinema concert production. 
"Boy With Luv feat. Halsey" is the biggest 24 hour debute in YouTube History.

The economy is growing because of them as they have contributed to an impressive large increase of tourism like no other before. BTS alone bring 3.7 billion dollars every year into the S.Korean economy. In Oct 2018 they were awarded the honorable ”Order Of Cultural Merit” by the S.Korean government and president. When they recieved their statuettes, each member was presented with their talents/skills and position in the group.

*Suga (Lead rapper, possesses solid rapping skills, contributes greatly to K-pop being loved by fans all over the world by showcasing incredible talents such as writing lyrics and composing songs).
*J-hope (Main dancer, in charge of the choreography of BTS, possesses excellent dance skills, plays a large role in gathering attention to the world, completing the powerful and elaborate performances of BTS etc).
The 4 vocalists are: 
*Jungkook (shown remarkable talents in all fields, including vocals, dance, songwriting and rap, contributed greatly to BTS to spreading out to the world together with Hallyu (the so called the Korean Wave aka Korean popular culture).
*Jimin (Lead Vocalist and Main dancer, acting as an all-around entertainer who possesses not only excellent dancing skills but also amazing vocals etc).
*Jin (Vocalist, shown multi-faceted talents through his deep emotional comprehension, unique vocals, participating in lyrics writing, leading the movement for the globalization of K-pop etc)
*V (Vocalist, singer/songwriter, charge of killing part of the songs with his deep charismatic voice, working to spread Hallyu all over the world etc). After recieving their medals all 7 members gave individual speeches.

Their hard work and multi-talents have made them won the biggest musical Korean awards (so called ”Daesangs”) in the K-music industry multiple times. BTS made an all-win 2019 when winning all the Daesangs in one night. Overall they are the most decorated K-artists ever. (Girl group ”Girl’s Generation” is in 2nd). Their performances (which are always different at every award show) they prepare so much for every year at these award shows are insane. 
BTS is invited to perform at this year’s Grammys 2020. The fact that BTS was completely ignored and snubbed though for any award was scandalous without a legit excuse. BTS had the best-selling album 2019 and hit youtube record with ”Boy with luv”. They litterally out-sold all the albums that were nominated for ”Album of the year”. BTS is high-end on all levels, which is something that alot of people have a hard time to admit or accept. Some said BTS aren’t American, but it shouldn’t matter.
